I'll come back after one.

612
00:49:51,738 --> 00:49:52,698
Sure.

613
00:50:28,066 --> 00:50:29,568
I've been waiting for you.

614
00:50:45,417 --> 00:50:48,378
Why have you when you had no idea
what I'd do to you?

615
00:50:49,254 --> 00:50:51,840
I knew you'd come to kill me.

616
00:50:53,008 --> 00:50:56,178
What are you up to this time around?

617
00:50:58,013 --> 00:50:59,598
Where's Mi-suk?

618
00:51:03,727 --> 00:51:05,771
Do you really not know

619
00:51:06,938 --> 00:51:08,440
where she's buried?

620
00:51:15,739 --> 00:51:17,741
I'm just like everyone else.

621
00:51:19,576 --> 00:51:21,161
I only found out

622
00:51:21,912 --> 00:51:24,164
that my father was a serial killer
through the news.

623
00:51:26,208 --> 00:51:27,959
Is that so hard to believe?

624
00:51:36,009 --> 00:51:37,719
I thought you'd come clean…

625
00:51:41,389 --> 00:51:44,142
when you kill me.

626
00:51:47,354 --> 00:51:48,980
Whether you believe me or not,

627
00:51:50,107 --> 00:51:52,317
I have no plans to spare you.

628
00:51:55,028 --> 00:51:57,531
Because you tried to ruin my life,

629
00:51:58,740 --> 00:52:00,534
and you're still capable of doing that.

630
00:52:02,035 --> 00:52:04,371
Lying in bed
and staring at the ceiling all day

631
00:52:04,454 --> 00:52:05,997
made me realize something.

632
00:52:07,415 --> 00:52:09,251
That everything I know about you

633
00:52:10,293 --> 00:52:12,087
is based on the rumors.

634
00:52:13,839 --> 00:52:14,756
And that…

635
00:52:18,677 --> 00:52:21,179
I could be wrong.

636
00:52:27,853 --> 00:52:29,729
I've killed an innocent person

637
00:52:30,897 --> 00:52:32,524
and brutally tortured you.

638
00:52:37,487 --> 00:52:39,072
You don't need to hesitate.

639
00:53:51,102 --> 00:53:54,648
I believe this cable tie
was used to bind his victims.

640
00:54:14,084 --> 00:54:15,252
I have a question.

641
00:54:21,633 --> 00:54:24,094
How did it feel to find out…

642
00:54:26,263 --> 00:54:27,764
that your wife had died?

643
00:54:31,184 --> 00:54:32,102
What?

644
00:54:35,272 --> 00:54:36,731
How did you feel…

645
00:54:38,108 --> 00:54:39,401
when your wife died?

646
00:54:40,568 --> 00:54:42,946
That's… That's…

647
00:54:44,030 --> 00:54:46,116
That's what you're curious about?

648
00:54:46,700 --> 00:54:47,617
Why?

649
00:54:50,245 --> 00:54:51,788
Why are you curious about that?

650
00:54:54,582 --> 00:54:56,501
You almost died in front of me.

651
00:54:58,128 --> 00:55:01,506
You don't know what kind of hell
I was in for those ten days.

652
00:55:02,882 --> 00:55:04,759
You'll never know.

653
00:55:12,100 --> 00:55:13,184
I want to know.

654
00:55:21,276 --> 00:55:22,527
I wanted to die.

655
00:55:24,696 --> 00:55:26,114
Then why didn't you?

656
00:55:26,823 --> 00:55:28,742
Because there was something I had to do.

657
00:55:32,412 --> 00:55:33,621
I wanted her…

658
00:55:36,416 --> 00:55:40,503
to rest in a safer
and more comfortable place.

659
00:55:41,755 --> 00:55:43,048
But she was already dead.

660
00:55:44,466 --> 00:55:45,967
What's the point in doing that?

661
00:55:51,931 --> 00:55:54,392
Because when people talk about her…

662
00:55:57,479 --> 00:55:59,189
they'll know where she's buried.

663
00:56:13,078 --> 00:56:14,245
Goodbye, then.

664
00:56:26,091 --> 00:56:28,927
Thank you so much for dressing
Park Gyeong-chun's wounds for me.

665
00:56:29,594 --> 00:56:31,554
His hands are cuffed. Why are you afraid?

666
00:56:32,263 --> 00:56:35,683
Because it somehow feels
like he's staring at me.

667
00:56:36,393 --> 00:56:38,686
What a scaredy-cat.

668
00:56:39,729 --> 00:56:44,359
Excuse me. Do you dress
Park Gyeong-chun's wounds twice a day?

669
00:56:44,442 --> 00:56:47,112
-Pardon?
-I'm the detective in charge.

670
00:56:49,489 --> 00:56:52,742
-We only do it once a day.
-And you've already done it today?

671
00:56:52,826 --> 00:56:54,786
Yes. I did it.

672
00:57:25,650 --> 00:57:27,277
You asked me last time…

673
00:57:33,032 --> 00:57:34,492
about that fish keychain.

674
00:57:40,623 --> 00:57:43,376
Someone gave it
to my sister at the funeral.

675
00:57:44,836 --> 00:57:46,212
And she gave it to me.

676
00:57:46,796 --> 00:57:48,465
Why didn't you tell me this sooner?

677
00:57:51,384 --> 00:57:53,511
Would you have believed me back then?

678
00:57:54,846 --> 00:57:57,515
You would've kidnapped her as well
and drowned her.

679
00:58:02,061 --> 00:58:03,229
Who could it have been?

680
00:58:05,023 --> 00:58:07,025
They intentionally gave it to her.

681
00:58:08,651 --> 00:58:09,486
But why?

682
00:58:11,988 --> 00:58:13,990
So you're saying that--

683
00:58:14,073 --> 00:58:17,827
Someone witnessed
Jung Mi-suk getting kidnapped,

684
00:58:17,911 --> 00:58:21,372
and I proved my father's alibi
for the time of the kidnapping.

685
00:58:22,457 --> 00:58:25,418
What if both of us told the truth?

686
00:58:27,045 --> 00:58:28,379
So you're saying

687
00:58:29,380 --> 00:58:31,257
that Do Min-seok really had an accomplice?

688
00:58:38,556 --> 00:58:40,558
I heard you have two months left.

689
00:58:42,352 --> 00:58:44,979
How about you quit
barking up the wrong tree this time around

690
00:58:45,647 --> 00:58:47,649
and chase after the real culprit?

691
00:58:49,484 --> 00:58:50,777
It's your choice.

692
00:58:54,781 --> 00:58:55,782
Hey.

693
00:58:56,824 --> 00:58:58,535
Take this out.

694
00:58:58,618 --> 00:59:01,037
I refuse to die. I refuse.

695
00:59:01,120 --> 00:59:03,665
Spare me.

696
00:59:05,333 --> 00:59:08,294
It's closed. You won't die.

697
00:59:18,429 --> 00:59:21,140
Why did you close it?

698
00:59:24,435 --> 00:59:26,854
You didn't tell anyone about me.

699
00:59:28,648 --> 00:59:29,941
You could have.

700
00:59:31,985 --> 00:59:33,027
Right.

701
00:59:33,987 --> 00:59:35,655
The police were curious…

702
00:59:37,657 --> 00:59:39,325
about why you had tortured me.

703
00:59:43,454 --> 00:59:45,582
Listen carefully to what I'm about to say.

704
00:59:59,178 --> 01:00:01,347
I've never seen him cry or laugh.

705
01:00:01,431 --> 01:00:04,100
He always spent time
with his father at the workshop.

706
01:00:04,183 --> 01:00:05,685
He was certainly not normal.

707
01:00:05,768 --> 01:00:08,813
I had told him numerous times
not to trust that kid.

708
01:00:17,363 --> 01:00:19,198
-Mommy…
-Oh, dear.

709
01:00:19,282 --> 01:00:22,744
Eun-ha, don't cry.

710
01:00:22,827 --> 01:00:24,329
Don't cry.

711
01:00:24,412 --> 01:00:27,081
I'll give you some food.

712
01:00:27,707 --> 01:00:29,208
Give me a minute.

713
01:00:32,962 --> 01:00:36,049
Mommy…

714
01:00:41,054 --> 01:00:44,015
Eun-ha, come here.

715
01:00:44,724 --> 01:00:47,226
I should hold you while standing up.

716
01:00:48,936 --> 01:00:50,021
Come on.

717
01:00:52,023 --> 01:00:54,150
-You don't need to come out. Sleep more.
-Mommy.

718
01:01:12,085 --> 01:01:16,172
At 9:00 a.m. today, Park Gyeong-chun,
the suspect in the Hoesin-dong Murder Case

719
01:01:16,255 --> 01:01:17,840
